{
  "texts": [
    "C. Real-time Error Detection and CorrectionReal-time error detection and correction algorithms have shown promising results in various AI-driven applications, from robotics to software automation [13], [24].",
    "Research in this domain has emphasized the algorithms' ability to instantly detect and rectify errors, which is crucial for maintaining the operational efficiency and accuracy of automated systems [25], [26].",
    "This approach is particularly beneficial for LLMs, as it allows for immediate corrections, thus preventing the compounding of errors over time and enhancing overall system reliability [27], [28].",
    "D. Error Correction in Non-English AI SystemsThe challenge of error correction in non-English AI systems has been a focal point of recent research, acknowledging the intricacies associated with diverse linguistic and cultural contexts [2], [29], [30].",
    "Studies have highlighted that error correction techniques optimized for English models often underperform when applied to other languages, necessitating tailored approaches [31], [32]."
  ]
}